title: Shares of several basic materials companies are trading lower following an increase in coronavirus cases in some US states that have reopened, leading to concerns of a second wave of the virus.

Shares of several basic material companies are trading lower as equities sell off following the recent rally. Stocks have rallied over the past week amid optimism towards the US economy reopening and investors have potentially taken some profits following run up. NOTE: Investors are awaiting the FOMC meeting on Wednesday.
